        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <salute>My dear Sir,—</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>From the well-known value of your several contributions to ornithology, &amp; for the extraordinary zeal, which you have for many years shown in the pursuit of natural science, I can not entertain the least doubt that you are well fitted to fill a higher post in the B. Museum, &amp; that you will there do excellent service.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>With my best wishes for your success | I am my d<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> S | Your vy faithfully | C. D <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">R. B. Sharpe— | Nov 24</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.1 From] <hi rend="italic">after</hi> ‘*I have much pleasure in expressing my opinion, [<hi rend="italic">del red crayon</hi>] that [<hi rend="italic">del blue crayon below</hi> ‘formed’ <hi rend="italic">blue crayon, del blue crayon</hi>] *from the extraordinary zeal you have shown for many years in pursuing natural [<hi rend="italic">del</hi>; ‘pursuing’ <hi rend="italic">above del</hi> ‘furthering’] History, [<hi rend="italic">del blue crayon</hi>]’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">1.1 well-known] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n3">1.1 several] <hi rend="italic">above del</hi> ‘many’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n4">1.1 for the] <hi rend="italic">after del red crayon</hi> ‘more [<hi rend="italic">interl</hi>] especially’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n5">1.2 for many] <hi rend="italic">after del blue crayon</hi> ‘now’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n6">1.2 the pursuit of] <hi rend="italic">blue crayon above del blue crayon</hi> ‘pursuing’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n7">1.3 can … doubt] <hi rend="italic">underl blue crayon</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n8">1.3 not] <hi rend="italic">interl red crayon</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n9">1.3 the least] <hi rend="italic">red crayon, above del</hi> ‘no’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n10">1.3 well] <hi rend="italic">blue crayon above del</hi> ‘wholly’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n11">1.4 excellent] <hi rend="italic">red crayon above del red crayon</hi> ‘real good’; ‘real’ <hi rend="italic">also del blue crayon</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n12">3.1 R. … 24] <hi rend="italic">added red crayon</hi> </note>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
